---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ProbabilitySimulator from '../../../components/diagrams/ProbabilitySimulator.svelte';
---

<Layout title="Data and Chance" lang="en" backHref="/explore-math/en/grade-6/" backLabel="← Grade 6">
	<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Data and Chance</h1>
	<p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-8">First steps in statistics and probability</p>

	<section class="prose max-w-none">
		<h2>Is it really random?</h2>
		<p>When you roll a die — is every number equally likely? Theoretically yes: each has probability 1/6 ≈ 16.7%. But what does it look like in practice?</p>

		<h3>🧪 Experiment: Dice Simulation</h3>
		<p>Roll many times and observe: the more you roll, the closer each number gets to 16.7%!</p>
	</section>

	<ProbabilitySimulator client:visible />

	<section class="prose max-w-none mt-8">
		<h3>💡 The Law of Large Numbers</h3>
		<p>With few rolls, anything can happen. But with <strong>many repetitions</strong>, the relative frequency approaches the theoretical probability.</p>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>Probability</strong> = favorable outcomes ÷ possible outcomes</li>
			<li>For a die: P(6) = 1/6</li>
			<li>In 100 rolls: expect about 16-17 sixes</li>
		</ul>
	</section>
</Layout>
